<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>There's a huge difference between respecting a camp, or a pull spot for a group, and expecting people to give you 1/4 of a zone to kite in for one person. If I settle into a spot and start pulling mobs for a half hour and a kiter shows up and bitches that i'm in his kite-path, he can go fuck himself. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Or as I've established, justifiably <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>fuck you</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. (Your words, not mine.)<br>
<br>
Largthemiserable:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>[...]Odd, because I did [read your posts],[...]<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well, the evidence really doesn't hold that up, as, again, shall be displayed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Face it, you've got a bard with a faggot name to begin with who can't pull while running in circles (which is something I can't figure out, if you can park your swarm by making a pet, what prevents you from charming near your pull site  )<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I addressed this. If you pull while your charming, your pet will be left behind. A given pet only lasts about 12 to 18 seconds. That means you won't be given accurate hp updates for when to break charm, and, when charm breaks (either because you broke it by pure blind luck, or they killed it) those mobs will likely be in the water somewhere you can't see, on the way toward where you're trying to pull.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>who can't kite his pulls in the vicinity of his camp so he goes where you can't even see his little circlejerk in action<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Well that's again not supported by the facts. To quote, yet again, an earlier passage, this one Liberachi's:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Well, anyway, I see this group (all from the same guild) come up and make camp in the middle of my pull through area.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If he can see them, they most certainly must have seen him.<br>
<br>
Although this is out of order, the first part of your statement makes a false implication; that his lack of skill determines his inability to kite in that camp.<br>
<br>
The geography of that area forbids it. Charm can't land when the mobs are in the water, and in order to swarm kite, you have to go in circles large enough such that they don't hit you. That specific locale has the above-water terrain shaped like an isthmus - making it impossible to have the mobs completely out of the water at all times.<br>
<br>
