1. The bard pulls mobs from area A, through area B, to area C<br>
     i. The bard can not kite in area A.<br>
     ii. The bard can not kite in area B.<br>
     iii. Area C is within visible range of area B.<br>
2. The bard kites in area C for 2 hours.<br>
3. Group sets up in area B.<br>
4. <br>
     1) Bard can not chat while kiting as that exposes him to danger.<br>
     2) Bard can not chat while kiting as that causes substantial loss of exp.<br>
     c) Bard can not communicate with the group while he is kiting.<br>
5. Bard finishes kiting 40 minutes after the group has set up in area B.<br>
6. Bard communicates with the group requesting them to move for their own safety.<br>
7. Group refuses to verify his claims, nor move from area B.<br>
8. Bard resumes kiting.<br>
9. Group dies while Bard pulls through Area B.<br>
10. The 'train' is justified.<br>
